					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If there are any consequences at all, usually it's something like getting your eBay seller account banned, rather than being sued for copyright infringement.<br /><br />I'm still kind of amazed that this made it past Kickstarter's review process: <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1348643050/nintendo-nes-retroplayernl-championship-2015" class="postlink">Nintendo NES: Retroplayer.nl championship 2015</a><br /><br />So anyhow, there is hope for people that want to ignore the law and make reproductions and stuff, I guess, but it's never without risk. As for whether it's moral/ethical, that's more of a personal question, I guess? You'll get a lot of variation on that question.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

